<!WA1><IMG SRC=http://www.eecs.umich.edu/~shriram/group/images/feather.gif></H1></CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=6>T</FONT SIZE>he <EM>NDR group</EM> at the <!WA2><A HREF="http://www.umich.edu">University of Michigan</A> is actively conducting research in diverse areas of VLSI design, testing and CAD.  We are part of the <!WA3><A HREF="http://www.eecs.umich.edu">Electrical Engineering and Computer Science</A> department of the <!WA4><A HREF="http://www.engin.umich.edu/college">College of Engineering</A>.  The group is headed by Professor <!WA5><A HREF="http://www.eecs.umich.edu/~mazum">Pinaki Mazumder</A>.  Current research thrusts are in the areas of Quantum Circuit Design, CAD,
Memory Testing, Built-In Self-Repair, and Flat Panel Display Electronics.
<P>
Quantum circuit development is a collaborative effort  with the Center for High Frequency Microelectronics at the University of Michigan.  The project is under the direction of Professor George I. Haddad, Chair, EECS department and is jointly funded by ARPA and URI.
<HR>
<FONT SIZE=5>Research Assistantships Available</FONT SIZE>
<BR>
Three (3) research assistantships are available.  Qualified students
should possess:
<UL>
<LI> Strong circuits background
<LI> Desire to do a Ph.D.
</UL>
Also desirable:
<UL>
<LI> Industrial Experience
</UL>
